channel.title: New to RSPS and I need help
channel.description:
So basically, I am using the MezzyScape 384 client/source/cache. I'm not new-new, as in my first time but new to creating my own. I somewhat know how to code and everything but I am having an error. After I changed the jdk version to mine, so I could run the client, it said "client updated, please reload." So I tried to compile.. and I got this message:
"Note: Recompile with Xlint:deprecation for details."
I googled that and everyone said it compiled but the code may break in the future relases of Java? I don't know, I still can't load the client. If anyone can help, that would be terrific. I apologize in advance if I sound stupid at all as I am a bit new to this. Thanks to anyone who can help though! :) I really want to play this, it looks pretty awesome.

item.title: New to RSPS and I need help
item.dc:creator: @runescape_sucks runescape sucks
item.description:
@runescape_sucks wrote:

That’s not an error, just a warning. (Boy, all hell will break loose when this is actually no longer available)

As for your client, the server is saying that there is most likely a UID or something like that, and your client is different, or their is a client version, and your client’s is different from the server’s.
